About Kiev Ukraine Medical University

Kyiv Medical University is one of the{" "} best medical university in Ukraine {" "} that was established in 1992. It establishes clinical and teaching base along with the introduction of latest technology. It offers practical exposure to students to get the required knowledge, skills to cater the demand of health-care industry. Industry exposure is offered to students through offshore internships. It has perfectly balanced curriculum meeting the need of Ministry of Health and Education of Ukraine. It is approved with the MCI & WHO.

Indian Student Admission Procedure

Indian students need to follow the below steps to take admission in Ukraine MBBS college:

  • {" "} The admissions at this University are carried out by laws of Ukraine followed by the legal status of foreigners and persons.
  • {" "} The students who get a state grant with respect to the international agreement, national programs, international obligations of Ukraine are eligible for the medical studies.
  • {" "} The submission of documents is started from 1st July until October 15th of an academic year.

Eligibility Criteria of Kiev Ukraine Medical University

The eligibility criteria of the students who want to{" "} study MBBS in the best medical university in Ukraine {" "} are as follows:

  • {" "} The students should have science in their 12th standard and should have an aggregate of 55% marks in physics, chemistry, and Biology.
  • {" "} The students should be at least 17 years of age to take admission in the best medical university in Ukraine.
  • {" "} The students should also qualify for the NEET exam with passing marks to apply for taking admission to{" "} Ukraine MBBS college.
  • {" "} The students should have English subject in their higher secondary.
  • {" "} The students must not be more than 25 years of age.
Requirements for MBBS Admission

The necessary documents for taking admission to{" "} Ukraine MBBS college are the following:

  • {" "} A complete filled application form with all accurate details.
  • {" "} Original and photocopies of Passport.
  • {" "} Birth certificates and other mandatory certificates must be submitted to the concerned authority.
  • {" "} Passport size (3cmX4cm) photographs.
  • {" "} Original and a photocopy of mark sheets of both 10th & 12th standard
  • {" "} A scorecard of NEFT (if required)
  • {" "} Transfer certificate from the previous school
  • {" "} Leaving certificate from the concerned school
  • {" "} A certificate of code of conduct must be submitted
  • {" "} The bank copy of guardians must be submitted which indicates that they have sufficient funds to pay the fees.
  • {" "} A medical checkup certificate is also essential

Kiev Ukraine Medical University Facility

Kiev Ukraine Medical University provides the following facilities:

  • {" "} It provides lecture halls, laboratories, library, hostel, canteens, playground, and hospitals under the roof all the amenities for the medical students.
  • {" "} The University provides a multicultural environment to the students.
  • {" "} It provides the art of research facilities and equipment to students.
  • {" "} It has an excellent system of hostel accommodation.
Kiev Ukraine Medical University Advantages for Indian Student

Kiev Ukraine Medical University provides the following advantages to the Indian students:

  • {" "} It offers a summer training program to students which provide international exposure and experience to students in the clinical field.
  • {" "} It provides real-time healthcare facilities to medical students during their undergraduate course.
  • {" "} The professors encourage the students to participate in student exchange programs which assist them to study methodologies in healthcare & research activities.
  • {" "} It conducts the training program in leading institutes of different countries.
